<section class="section-paragraph section-faqs">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Social Media Specialiast FAQs</h2>
        <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage" class="row">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                    <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse1">
                        <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What are Instagram Ads?</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse1" class="collapse">
                        <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                            <p>Instagram ads are sponsored posts or stories that a business uses to promote products or services to targeted Instagram users. They can resemble a regular Instagram post, except for the addition of a “Sponsored” tag and call-to-action option, and will appear on the targeted user’s news or story feed. </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                    <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse2">
                        <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">Why are Instagram Ads important?</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse2" class="collapse">
                        <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                            <p>Instagram reports that with 800 million active users, 60% of people discover new products, and 75% take action from seeing a post. Instagram uses Facebook’s demographic data to reach specific segments based on their interests and behaviours and can be a cost-effective tool to increase engagement and conversions. </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                    <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse3">
                        <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What’s the difference between Instagram and Facebook Ads?</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse3" class="collapse">
                        <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                            <p>Although both platforms use Facebook’s advertising system to target users, the interactions and demographics are different and work to reach different audiences. Facebook’s user demographics are the widest out of all the social media platforms, while 55% of users are between the ages of 18-29. Depending on your business’s offerings and targeted users, both platforms can be used separately or together to reach a wider audience.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                    <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse4">
                        <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">What are the types of Instagram Ads?</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse4" class="collapse">
                        <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                            <p>Instagram’s ad formats include stories, photo, video, carousel, explore, IGTV, and Instagram Shopping ads. Each ad has different call-to-action options and caters to different business objectives.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                    <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse5">
                        <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">How can I get started with Instagram Ads?</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse5" class="collapse">
                        <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                            <p>Instagram Ads form a part of a holistic digital strategy that drives traffic and sales for your business. If you have a Facebook page for your business, you can create an Instagram Business page to get started. For help on creating your comprehensive Instagram Ad strategy, contact our digital marketing strategists today. </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                    <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse6">
                        <h3 itemprop="name" class="h3-accordion-title-fpau">Will Instagram Ads benefit my business?</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse6" class="collapse">
                        <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                            <p>Instagram has over 500 million daily users. For almost every business, there is a considerable pool of potential customers waiting to be discovered on Instagram. With First Page behind the wheel, you can run compelling ads on one of the world’s biggest digital platforms and get your product or service in front of more eyes than ever before. </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
